Nagel Tells Welt S&P’s Germany Rating Watch Is ‘Unconvincing’

-- B y   J e f f   B l a c k
-- 
2011-12-06T18:54:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-06/nagel-tells-welt-s-p-s-germany-rating-watch-is-unconvincing-.html
The justification for the credit
rating downgrade warning to  Germany  yesterday by  Standard &
Poor’s  is “unconvincing,” Bundesbank board member Joachim Nagel said,  Die Welt  newspaper reported, citing an interview.  Nagel said the warning would become irrelevant when
European leaders delivered what financial markets expect of
them, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jeff Black in Frankfurt at 
